				\begin{document}$$\{A,C,G,T\}$$\end{document}{A,C,G,T} with an additional “line break” character marking the ends of assembly fragments (chromosomes, scaffolds, or contigs). The set S(G) of all contiguous DNA sequences present in G comprises all substrings of G that do not contain a line break as well as their reverse complements. DNA sequences are compared by a metric distance function d, which in practise is derived from sequence alignments.

